## Diagnosis

The "Yilan Gao" logo wraps to two lines under viewport squeeze. Looking at `Navigation.module.scss`, the CSS has the **right intent but is structurally incomplete** — resulting in a defense that fails under certain browser reflow conditions:

1. **`.navInner` is missing `flex-wrap: nowrap`** — the flex row is allowed to wrap, so under pressure the logo link can drop to a second line even though its children have `white-space: nowrap`
2. **`.logo` has `flex-shrink: 0` but no `min-width: max-content`** — `flex-shrink: 0` prevents compression but doesn't prevent the browser from collapsing the element's box below `max-content` in certain layout contexts
3. **`.links` has `min-width: 0` but no `overflow: hidden`** — the tagline text can force the container wider than its allocated share, which in turn triggers the logo reflow

---

## Root Cause

**AP-066 — Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text.** The three-layer defense (container `flex-wrap: nowrap` + item `flex-shrink: 0` + item `min-width: max-content`) must be applied together. Having `flex-shrink: 0` alone without `flex-wrap: nowrap` on the parent is an incomplete guard — the flex row can still reflew the logo onto line 2 via row-wrapping even when the item itself won't compress. This is the exact gap between "the logo won't squish" and "the logo won't move."

---

## Fix

Three files change: the component SCSS (runtime fix), the anti-patterns catalog (amend AP-066 with the priority-hierarchy rule), and the feedback log (mark FB-146 resolved).

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

